Summary 11/21/2018¶

Learning Experiments¶

Preliminary stuff:¶

  • For every instance $i$:
    • First run the column heuristic i.e. compute $CG(i,\emptyset)$.
    • Then for each instance, take it's optimal columns and share with $i$. i.e. compute $CG(i,j)$.
    • Populate "improvement matrices" $$M_\text{abs}(i,j) \gets CG(i,j) - CG(i,\emptyset)$$ and $$M_\text{pct}(i,j) \gets \frac{CG(i,j) - CG(i,\emptyset)}{IP(i)}$$.
  • From $M$ matrices, determine similar/dissimiliar pairs for feeding in metric learning algorithms. Options below:
    1. Set $u,l$ such that $M_\text{abs}(i,j) > u$ means $i,j$ are similar, $M_\text{abs}(i,j) < l$ are different.
    2. Same, but with $M_\text{pct}$.
    3. Pick $k,l$. For each $i$, set the top $k$ M(i,j) to be similar, and $M(i,j) < l$ to different. If both are true for some $i,j$, then different takes precedence.
  • Resolving similarity/dissimilarity conflicts
    • Since $M$ matrices are not symmetric but similarity/dissimilarity is a symmetric concept, we need a way to resolve this
    • Current heuristic: If one of $(i,j), (j,i)$ is "similar", then $(i,j)$ is similar. If neither are similar and one of them is "dissimilar", then dissimilar.

Metric Learning stuff:¶

  • Took 100 instances.
  • Features used for Metric Learning
    • ports: rates/inventory/capacities
    • vessel classes: number of vessels, number fixed starting locations
    • ports x vessel classes: number fixed starting
    • column generation: $CG(i,\emptyset)$ minus LP relaxation.
  • Learning Methods tested
    • Classic MMC model (Mahalanobis Metric learning for Clustering, first metric learning method) doesn't seem to work.
    • Tried ITML instead (Information Theoretic Metric Learning).
  • Methodology
    • Goal: An approximation of real work-flow that's quick to run
    • For each instance $i$, find 5 closest instances according to computed metric.
    • Take the best $CG(i,j)$ out of these five
  • Observations
    • best results obtained
      • relative measure for choosing similarities with thresholds of 20%, 10%
      • Compared this result against standard Euclidean metric 
        Overall best percentage: 70.6

def extract_mirp_features(mirp):
    rates = [p_data.rate for p_data in mirp.ports.values()]
    feature_vec = rates
    return feature_vec

n_ports = 9
n_vcs = 4
n_periods = 30
seed = 1
n_instances = 1000

n = 50
test_range = range(50)

lp_dir = '.'

base_folder = '%s/ports%d_vcs%d_t%d_seed%d_n%d' % (lp_dir,
                                                   n_ports,
                                                   n_vcs,
                                                   n_periods,
                                                   seed,
                                                   n_instances)

instance_files = ['%s/instance_i%d_data.txt' % (base_folder, i)
                  for i in test_range]

def feature_distances(instances_files, test_range):
    print("[ Extracting Routes ]")
    instance_rates = {}
    for i in test_range:
        instance_file = instance_files[i]
        mirp = generator.load(instance_file)
        instance_rates[i] = np.array(extract_mirp_features(mirp))

    dist = np.zeros((n,n))
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            dist[i,j] = np.linalg.norm(instance_rates[i]-instance_rates[j])

    plt.figure()
    plt.imshow(dist)

def preprocess(n, data, normalize=True):
    matrix = np.zeros((n,n))
    gap = [data['baseline'][i] - data['relax_col_gen'][i]
           for i in range(n)]
    
    for i,j in itertools.product(range(n), range(n)):
        matrix[i,j] = data['baseline'][i] - data['seeded'][i][j]['ip_obj']
    
    if normalize:
        for i,j in itertools.product(range(n), range(n)):
            matrix[i,j] = matrix[i,j] / gap[i]
    
    return matrix


def process(n, data):
    matrix = np.zeros((n,n))
    relaxgap = [data['baseline'][i] - data['relax_col_gen'][i]
           for i in range(n)]
    
    ipgap = [data['baseline'][i] - data['original_ip'][i]
             for i in range(n)]

def laplacian(M):
    n = M.shape[0]
    A = M + M.transpose()
    Lap_A = np.diag(np.dot(A,np.ones(n))) - A
    return Lap_A

def get_order(M):
    L_A = laplacian(M)
    w, v = np.linalg.eig(L_A)
    fiedler = v[:,1]
    return np.argsort(fiedler)

n = 50
pickle_file = 'debug100.p'
with open(pickle_file, 'rb') as f:
    data = pickle.load(f)

print(data.keys())
seeded_data = data['seeded']

for instance_idx in range(n):
    instance_data = seeded_data[instance_idx]
    print("Processing Instance %d ..." % instance_idx)
    print("- true ip obj: %.2f" % (data['original_ip'][instance_idx]))
    print("- baseline ip obj: %.2f" % (data['baseline'][instance_idx]))
    print("- column gen relax obj: %.2f" % (data['relax_col_gen'][instance_idx]))
    # ip diff is with respect to baseline, positive is good
    for i in range(n):
        combo_data = instance_data[i]
        n_trivial_routes = 0
        n_seeded_routes = 0
        n_cg_routes = 0
        for lambda_names in combo_data['lambda'].values():
            for lambda_name in lambda_names:
                if lambda_name in combo_data['lambda_names']['seeded']:
                    n_seeded_routes += 1
                elif lambda_name in combo_data['lambda_names']['trivial']:
                    n_trivial_routes += 1
                else:
                    n_cg_routes += 1
        print("    (%d,%d) -- rounds: %d, routes: (%d,%d,%d,%d), relax: %.2f, ip diff: %.2f, percent gap closed: %.2f"
              % (instance_idx, i,
                 combo_data['rounds'],
                 combo_data['n_routes'],n_trivial_routes, n_seeded_routes, n_cg_routes,
                 combo_data['relax_obj'],
                 data['baseline'][instance_idx] - combo_data['ip_obj'],
                 100*(data['baseline'][instance_idx] - combo_data['ip_obj'])/(data['baseline'][instance_idx] - data['original_ip'][instance_idx])))
    print("")

                  threshold_type='percent',
                  threshold_yes=0.2, threshold_no=0.1):
    n_test = len(test_range)
    M = np.zeros((n_test,n_test))
    seeded_data = cg_data['seeded']
    for i in range(n_test):
        instance_idx = test_range[i]
        instance_data = seeded_data[instance_idx]
        gap = cg_data['baseline'][instance_idx] - cg_data['original_ip'][instance_idx]
        ip_diffs = [cg_data['baseline'][instance_idx] - instance_data[test_range[j]]['ip_obj'] 
                    for j in range(n_test)]
        for j in range(n_test):    
            if i == j:
                continue
            gap_closed = ip_diffs[j] / gap
            if threshold_type == 'percent':
                if gap_closed >= threshold_yes:
                    M[i,j] = 1
                elif gap_closed <= threshold_no and M[i,j] == 0:
                    M[i,j] = -1
            elif threshold_type == 'abs':
                ip_diff = ip_diffs[j]
                if ip_diff >= threshold_yes:
                    M[i,j] = 1
                elif ip_diff <= threshold_no and M[i,j] == 0:
                    M[i,j] = -1
            elif threshold_type == 'top':
                if gap_closed <= threshold_no and M[i,j] == 0:
                    M[i,j] = -1 
            else:
                print("invalid threshold type")
                return
        if threshold_type == 'top':
            a = np.array(ip_diffs)
            row_indices = sorted(range(len(a)), key=lambda k: a[k], reverse=True)[1:1+threshold_yes]
            #print(a[row_indices])
            for j in row_indices:
                if M[i,j] > -1:
                    M[i,j] = 1 

    A = []
    B = []
    C = []
    D = []
    for i in range(n_test):
        for j in range(i+1,n_test):
            if M[i,j] == 1 or M[j,i] == 1:
                A.append(i)
                B.append(j)
            elif M[i,j] == -1 and M[j,i] == -1:
                C.append(i)
                D.append(j)
                
    A = np.array(A).astype(int)
    B = np.array(B).astype(int)
    C = np.array(C).astype(int)
    D = np.array(D).astype(int)

    return A,B,C,D

def bottom_k_indices(row, n, k, reverse):
    row_indices = sorted(range(len(row)), key=lambda i: row[i], reverse=reverse)[1:1+k]
    return row_indices  

for X_fitted in X_fitted_list:
    #X_fitted = mmc.transform(X)
    #print(X_fitted[0:5,0:5])
    #print(X[0:5,0:5])
    fitted_distance = euclidean_distances(X_fitted)
    original_distance = euclidean_distances(X)

    #print(fitted_distance[0:5,0:5])
    #print(original_distance[0:5,0:5])
    
    diffs = []
    gaps = []
    improvements_best = []
    improvements_euc = []
    improvements_cov = []
    improvements_ml = []

    for test_idx in range(n):
        #print("Instance %d" % test_idx)
        a = matrix[test_idx,0:n]
        a_indices = bottom_k_indices(a, n, 5, True)
        b_indices = bottom_k_indices(fitted_distance[test_idx,0:n], n, 5, False)
        c_indices = bottom_k_indices(original_distance[test_idx,0:n], n, 5, False)
        
        #print(a)
        #print(fitted_distance[test_idx,0:n])
        #print(original_distance[test_idx,0:n])
        
        #print(c_indices)
        #print(b_indices)
        #d_indices = bottom_k_indices(cov_distance[test_idx,0:n], n, 5, False)

        text = "[%.1f %.1f] [%.1f %.1f] [%.1f %.1f]" % (max(a[a_indices]),min(a[a_indices]),
                                                  max(a[b_indices]),min(a[b_indices]),
                                                  max(a[c_indices]),min(a[c_indices]))
        #print(text)
        gap = max(a)
        improve_best = max(a[a_indices])
        improve_ml = max(a[b_indices])
        improve_euc = max(a[c_indices])
        #improve_cov = max(a[d_indices])

        improvements_best.append(improve_best)
        improvements_euc.append(improve_euc)
        improvements_ml.append(improve_ml)
        #improvements_cov.append(improve_cov)

        gaps.append(gap)

        #print("%.1f,%.1f" % (diff, gap))

    ml_vs_euc = [improvements_ml[i] - improvements_euc[i] for i in range(n)]
    #ml_vs_cov = [improvements_ml[i] - improvements_cov[i] for i in range(n)]

    print("Overall best percentage: %.1f" % (100*sum(improvements_best[i]/gaps[i] for i in range(n))/n))
    print("Overall best absolute: %.1f" % (sum(improvements_best)/n))
    print("Overall euc percentage: %.1f" % (100*sum(improvements_euc[i]/gaps[i] for i in range(n))/n))

    print("Overall Improvement euc absolute: %.1f" % (sum(ml_vs_euc)/n))
